div.span: We believe elevating where you live is about blending it seamlessly with how you live. We go to great lengths designing amenities and choosing locations that put everything within reach. Where you live, is where you come alive.Avalon Warner Place, home to the beautiful Woodland Hills apartments, is just minutes from Woodland Hills, the Warner Center business district, the Santa Monica Mountains and a wonderful array of shopping and dining. In addition, these brand new one-, two- and three-bedroom luxury apartments come equipped with designer kitchens featuring a breakfast bar and maple finish cabinetry. Upgrade any home to Furnished+ and enjoy the convenience of turnkey living.Residents can also take advantage of Avalon's fantastic amenities, such as relaxing in our outdoor pool and spa, enjoying a workout in our fitness center, or taking time out to catch up with friends and neighbors in the lounge. This is not just apartment living. This is living up.WOODLAND HILLS APARTMENTS BY AVALON The Woodland Hills apartment rentals share their neighborhood with a variety of fine restaurants and shopping districts. The Westfield Promenade and local grocery stores are only a fraction of a mile away from the apartments, while Roy's Hawaiian, Ruth's Chris Steakhouse, and Fleming’s Prime Steakhouse are a stone’s throw away as well. Woodland HIlls also has a strong community base with many highly-ranked elementary, middle and high schools in the area. Residents who work in the Warner Center business district benefit from a brief daily commute, ensuring your entire experience in Woodland Hills is comfortable and convenient. Our Woodland Hills apartments for rent also provide easy access to Malibu Beach, Santa Monica and all of Los Angeles.WOODLAND HILLS APARTMENT COMMUNITY When you choose the Woodland Hills apartments as your new home, you will be able to enjoy the benefits of our special plan called the Avalon Advantage. This program includes a 30-day move-in guarantee, a maintenance response guarantee, and a national relocation program. Avalon prides itself on being able to deliver a luxury greater Los Angeles experience to its Warner Place residents. From charming Woodland Hills apartment rentals with everything from designer kitchens to a 24-hour maintenance guarantee, Avalon delivers a central location that fits your lifestyle.So hurry and get your perfect home today! Contact us to schedule an appointment and find a whole new world of Los Angeles apartments for rent.

div.h2: The service. The standards. The life.

a.div: Great service is one of the things we think about most. We start with selecting passionate people. Then we let them put that passion to work. Our people are a vital part of what shapes the character of each Avalon community.

We strive to align our standards with yours, delivering an experience that lives up to them. We know you've put a lot into getting to where you are in life. We believe where you live should reflect that. So we put ourselves into making sure it does.

Effortless. Enjoyable. Truly comfortable living is both. That's why we go out of our way to choose locations and to design amenities that put so much within reach. So you can live easy without even trying.

div.div: Room dimensions, square footage, and features shown on the floor plan drawings are approximate and may vary between individual apartments that have similar layouts. Furniture shown on the floor plan drawings is representative and individual apartments come unfurnished unless specified otherwise. Quoted rent is per month for new move-ins to the community, based on the move-in date selected. Pricing may vary based on lease term. Quoted rent does not including other fees and charges that may be part of your lease (i.e. utilities, parking, etc.). Please contact the community for details. Prior to signing a lease, quoted rent, specials, availability, and other terms and conditions are subject to change without notice. Washington State - We require our own screening and do not accept comprehensive reusable tenant screening reports.
